Package eu.opends.basics

Class MapObjectOD

java.lang.Object
eu.opends.basics.MapObject
eu.opends.basics.MapObjectOD
public class MapObjectOD
extends MapObject
This class represents an additional map object (c.f. class MapObject) as it is used within class MapFactory in order to place spatial objects on the map. Instead of a given translation, the object will be placed relative to an OpenDRIVE object. Thus, the map object needs to be placed AFTER the initialization of all OpenDRIVE objects.
Author:
Rafael Math

  • Constructor Details

    • MapObjectOD

      public MapObjectOD​(java.lang.String name, com.jme3.scene.Spatial spatial, java.lang.String roadID, float s, float lateralOffset, float verticalOffset, com.jme3.math.Quaternion rotation, com.jme3.math.Vector3f scale, boolean isVisible, boolean addToMapNode, java.lang.String collisionShape, float mass, java.lang.String modelPath, java.lang.String collisionSound, ReferenceObjectParams referenceObjectParams)
      Creates a new map object which can either be a static or dynamic map object (c.f. related sub classes) and provides setter and getter methods for all fields.
      Parameters:
      name - Name of the map object.
      spatial - Spatial nodes to add to the scene graph.
      roadID - Location (road) where the nodes should be added.
      s - Location (longitudinal offset from road) where the nodes should be added.
      lateralOffset - Location (lateral offset from road) where the nodes should be added.
      verticalOffset - Location (vertical offset from road) where the nodes should be added.
      rotation - Rotation of the spatial node.
      scale - Scaling vector of the spatial node.
      isVisible - Defines whether the object is visible to the driver.
      addToMapNode - Defines whether model will be added to map node or scene node
      collisionShape - Defines whether the car can collide with the object.
      mass - Mass of the dynamic map object.
      modelPath - Path to model files
      collisionSound - Sound played when driver car collides with object
